rComments: Best teacher I have had at uiuc and I don't like math at all.  She was very clear in her presentation and showing up to her lecture is essential although not required.
IT IS HARDER THAN YOU THINK IT SHOULD BE

She was great! The only professor I have had so far that I have recommended to people. If you take 286 and can take it with her, you should. Exam questions pretty much follow the notes exactly, so study with the notes and figure out how to do each problem and you should be fine.

Easy to talk with and class was interesting. Always really excited and quirky which isn't that common in uni instructors; great attitude towards everyone. Go to office hours for written homework if you don't understand something. She does a great job at explaining and 9/10 times you'll have the answer at the end. Attend the "lecture" classes.

She teaches well. But the way she runs the class is not like other math classes here. The logistics of the class were very ambiguous and run in a very non-transparent way. No exam solutions given so you don't know what you did wrong. No past exams to hel p you study. No exam statistics posted... You're basically in the dark all semester.

The class is fairly simple and enjoyable. Just go to class, do the homework and make sure you understand everything and you'll do alright. She is very good at teaching and explains things in a straight to the point way. I'm happy I ended up in the mathematica section. I think knowing mathematica is a very valuable skill to have.
Good professor... She explains things in a straight forward manor.

Excellent math professor.  She is phenomenal at explaining topics and is an engaging lecturer.  Tests are difficult, but you learn loads in her course.  Plus, get an extra credit hour for learning Mathematica!
